symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to feel spongy or hard, leading to extended braking distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
